Task: How to build feedback loop with rxRust

 <p>With the rxRust crate nearing version 1.0 I wanted to give the ReactiveX concept a try. As one finger exercise I wanted to try a feedback loop on the example of a  simple rs-flipflop made of two NANDs.</p>
<p>My minimal, non working, example code only contains the dependency <code>rxrust = &quot;1.0.0-rc.2&quot;</code> in Cargo.toml and the following main.rs:</p>
<pre class="lang-rust prettyprint-override"><code>use rxrust::prelude::*;
use std::convert::Infallible;

type Type = LocalBoxedObservableClone&lt;'static, bool, Infallible&gt;;

fn nand(name: String, a: Type, b: Type) -&gt; Type {
    a.combine_latest(b, |a, b| (a, b))
        .distinct()
        .tap(move |(a, b)| print!(&quot;nand {name} ({a}, {b})&quot;))
        .map(|(a, b)| !(a &amp; b))
        .tap(|v| println!(&quot; = {v}&quot;))
        .box_it_clone()
}

fn flipflop(s: Type, r: Type) -&gt; (Type, Type) {
    let mut s2 = Local::behavior_subject::&lt;bool, Infallible&gt;(false);
    let mut r2 = Local::behavior_subject::&lt;bool, Infallible&gt;(false);

    let s2_box = s2.clone().box_it_clone();
    let r2_box = r2.clone().box_it_clone();

    let q1 = nand(&quot;s&quot;.to_string(), s, s2_box).box_it_clone();
    let q2 = nand(&quot;r&quot;.to_string(), r, r2_box).box_it_clone();

    q1.clone().subscribe(move |a| r2.next(a));
    q2.clone().subscribe(move |a| s2.next(a)); // RefCell already borrowed

    (q1, q2)
}

fn main() {
    let mut s = Local::behavior_subject::&lt;bool, Infallible&gt;(true);
    let mut r = Local::behavior_subject::&lt;bool, Infallible&gt;(true);

    let result: (Type, Type) = flipflop(s.clone().box_it_clone(), r.clone().box_it_clone());

    result
        .0
        .combine_latest(result.1, |q1, q2| (q1, q2))
        .subscribe(|(q1, q2)| println!(&quot;({q1:?}, {q2:?})&quot;));

    // (s: true, r: true) -&gt; (q1: x, q2: x)
    s.next(false); // (s: false, r: true) -&gt; (q1: true, q2: false)
    s.next(true); // (s: true, r: true) -&gt; (q1: true, q2: false)

    r.next(false); // (s: true, r: false) -&gt; (q1: false, q2: true)
    r.next(true); // (s: true, r: true) -&gt; (q1: false, q2: true)
}
</code></pre>
<p>The taps show that one event gets fed back into nand s and then panicks on line 26 with the message &quot;RefCell already borrowed.</p>
<p>How to do it right?</p>


